.TH BBX 1 "2026" "bbx sqlite toolkit pro" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bbx \- SQLite-backed CLI for organizing bug bounty artifacts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python3 bbx.py
.I command program [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
bbx imports existing outputs from recon, crawling, and HTTP capture tools, stores them in SQLite, ranks interesting rows, supports tagging, and can export correlation graphs.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init <path>
Initialize a workspace and database.
.TP
.B import-har <program> <file>
Import a Burp-compatible HAR file.
.TP
.B rank <program>
Rescore requests and discovered URLs.
.TP
.B top <program> [--limit N] [--format text|json|csv]
Show top-ranked requests.
.TP
.B interesting-urls <program> [--limit N] [--format text|json|csv]
Show top-ranked discovered URLs.
.TP
.B tag-add <program> <entity_type> <entity_id> <tag> [--note TEXT]
Add a tag to a row.
.TP
.B tag-remove <program> <entity_type> <entity_id> <tag>
Remove a tag.
.TP
.B tags <program> [--entity-type TYPE] [--tag TAG] [--format text|json|csv]
List tags.
.TP
.B new-finding <program> <slug>
Create a Markdown finding template and track it in SQLite.
.TP
.B set-finding-status <program> <slug> <status>
Update finding status.
.TP
.B list-findings <program> [--format text|json|csv]
List tracked findings.
.TP
.B graph <program> [--format mermaid|dot|json] [--out PATH]
Export a correlation graph.
.TP
.B export <program> <table> [--format json|csv]
Export a SQLite table.
.TP
.B summarize <program> [--format text|json|csv]
Show per-table counts.
.TP
.B db-stats <program> [--format text|json|csv]
Show DB counts and top hosts.
.SH IMPORTERS
.TP
.B ingest-subfinder, ingest-amass, ingest-httpx, ingest-katana, ingest-gau, ingest-wayback, ingest-naabu, ingest-ffuf, ingest-nuclei
Import existing tool outputs.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/bbx/<program>/bbx.sqlite3
Workspace database.
.TP
.I ~/bbx/<program>/graphs/
Graph exports.
.TP
.I ~/bbx/<program>/exports/
JSON and CSV exports.
.SH AUTHOR
Generated by OpenAI

.SH FILTERING
The following commands support filtering flags:
.B top
,
.B interesting-urls
,
.B export
, and
.B graph
.

.TP
.B --tag TAG
Only include rows tagged with TAG.

.TP
.B --host HOST
Only include rows matching HOST.

.TP
.B --min-score N
Only include rows with score >= N.

.TP
.B --tool NAME
Only include rows imported from the named tool when available.

.SH NEW FILTERS
The following filters are available on selected commands:
- B--containsR case-insensitive substring match
- B--path-prefixR restrict by URL path prefix
- B--statusR exact status match where available

.SH LAB-ONLY SCAN COMMANDS
.TP
.B scan-register-url <program> <url>
Register a URL as a scan asset.
.TP
.B scan-plan <program> [--profile safe-recon]
Queue scan checks for matching imported URLs.
.TP
.B scan-queue <program> --asset-id N --check NAME
Queue a single check manually.
.TP
.B scan-run <program> [--limit N]
Run queued checks against allowlisted hosts only.
.TP
.B scan-results <program>
Show recorded scan runs.
.TP
.B scan-findings <program>
Show findings emitted by scan checks.


## Layout note

`bbx.py` is now a tiny entrypoint. The CLI logic lives in `bbx/cli.py`, path helpers in `bbx/paths.py`, output helpers in `bbx/output.py`, and scoring logic in `bbx/scoring.py`.


## New reliability commands

- `bbx doctor <workspace>` checks workspace layout, DB presence, allowlist, scan profiles, and presets.
- `bbx validate-import <kind> <file>` validates supported import file shapes before ingest.
- CLI output formats now consistently use `text`, `json`, or `csv`.
